{"type":"section","nativeType":"section","number":"7708","heading":"Network for Earthquake Engineering Simulation","label":"7708 Network for Earthquake Engineering Simulation","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7708","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/ch86","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7708","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":["Editorial Notes","Amendments2004—Subsec. (b)(5) to (9). added pars. (5) to (9).Pub. L. 108–360"],"amendments":["Amendments2004—Subsec. (b)(5) to (9). added pars. (5) to (9).Pub. L. 108–360"],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"a","heading":"Establishment","label":"a Establishment","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7708/a","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7708","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7708%2Fa","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":"The Director of the National Science Foundation shall establish the George E. Brown, Jr. Network for Earthquake Engineering Simulation that will upgrade, link, and integrate a system of geographically distributed experimental facilities for earthquake engineering testing of full-sized structures and their components and partial-scale physical models. The system shall be integrated through networking software so that integrated models and databases can be used to create model-based simulation, and the components of the system shall be interconnected with a computer network and allow for remote access, information sharing, and collaborative research.","notes":[],"amendments":[],"effectiveDate":null,"children":[]},{"type":"subsection","nativeType":"subsection","number":"b","heading":"Authorization of appropriations","label":"b Authorization of appropriations","identifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7708/b","parentIdentifier":"/us/usc/t42/s7708","sourceUrl":"https://uscode.house.gov/view.xhtml?req=%2Fus%2Fusc%2Ft42%2Fs7708%2Fb","sourceRelease":"119-100","text":null,"notes":[],"amendments":[],"effe